  <abstract>
    <p>
      A guide to text analysis within the tidy data framework, using the
      tidytext package and other tidy tools in R.
    </p>
  </abstract>

  <preface xml:id="preface-ptx-version">
    <title>Note on This PreTeXt Edition</title>

    <p>
      This is a <url href="https://pretextbook.org/" visual="pretextbook.org">PreTeXt</url>
      conversion of <em>Text Mining with R: A Tidy Approach</em>, originally written by
      <url href="https://juliasilge.com/" visual="juliasilge.com">Julia Silge</url> and
      <url href="http://varianceexplained.org/" visual="varianceexplained.org">David Robinson</url>.
      The original work is available online at
      <url href="https://www.tidytextmining.com/" visual="tidytextmining.com">tidytextmining.com</url>
      and was published by O'Reilly Media. The original GitHub repository for the book source is at
